The channel Statistics command, cs, reports data on all or part of a
stereo file.  The command may be qualified by one or a pair of initial
addresses to limit the portion of the file to be reported.  The user is
shown the correlation coefficient between the two channels, and the sound
level, the maximum excursions in the negative and the positive direction,
and the value of a possible DC component in the channel.  To report the
entire file, use one of these equivalent forms: ",cs" or "1,$cs".

